# AI Chat Module Context

## Goal

Build a modular AI chat system where users can chat with AI assistants, switch between bots, and organize conversations into context-aware groups.

## Core Use Cases

- Users create chat groups for different topics or workflows.
- Each group has a shared context that is applied to every chat in that group.
- Users can start multiple chats inside a single group and keep context consistent.
- Users can switch bot providers per chat without changing the chat workflow.
- Initial bot support is Gemini only, with architecture ready for additional bots later.

## Product Rules

- Every chat belongs to exactly one group.
- A group-level context is included in all prompts sent from chats in that group.
- Chat-specific instructions can be added and should be merged with group context.
- Users can change the selected bot for a chat at any time.
- The first release must default to Gemini while preserving a provider-agnostic design.

## Data Modeling Guidance

- Treat groups, chats, and messages as separate entities.
- Store group context as structured text that can be versioned or edited.
- Keep provider-specific settings isolated from provider-agnostic chat state.
- Use stable IDs for groups, chats, messages, and provider configurations.
- Preserve enough metadata to reconstruct prompt context used for any response.

## Near-Term Scope

- Group CRUD with editable shared context.
- Chat CRUD within groups.
- Message history per chat.
- Gemini provider integration.
- Bot selector UI scaffolded for future providers (single Gemini option initially).
